FIGURE 1.
Photomicrographs of 

Ceratomyxa

sp. 1
from the gall bladder of 

Oblada melanura

. (A–E) Disporic sub-spherical to spherical plasmodia (
p
) containing each one two identical spores surrounded with vary refractive granules (
g
), Notice the presence of two capsulogenic nuclei (
cn)
and numerous sporoplasmosomes (
spp
). (F) Fresh smear contains disporic plasmodia (
p
) and Mature spores (
s
). (G) mature spore in sutural view showing the spherical polar capsules (
pc
), the straight suture line (
sl
), the sporoplasmic nuclei (
sn
), the capsulogenic nuclei (
cn
) and the unequal shell valves. (H) mature spore in lateral view. Scale bar = 20 µm in F; 10 µm in A–E, G–H.
